<h2 id="short-answer">Short answer</h2>
<p><em>Should I use a Cache to solve my current problem?</em></p>
<p><strong>No</strong>, but this answer might be wrong because it was cached ;)</p>
<h2 id="cache-optimization-calculator">Cache Optimization Calculator</h2>
<div>
    <div class="formcontainer">
        <div class="inlineform">
            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="rs"
                           type="number"
                           min="0.0"
                           max="100.0"
                           step="5"
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="Percentage 0-100" value="80"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="rs">Probability to find data in cache (0-100)</label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="cache-read"
                           type="number"
                           min="0.0"
                           step="100"
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="Milliseconds" value="100"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="cache-read">Average time to read from Cache (ms).</label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="cache-write"
                           type="number"
                           min="0.0"
                           step="100"
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="Milliseconds" value="200"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="cache-write">Average time to write to Cache (ms).</label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="operation"
                           type="number"
                           min="0.0"
                           step="100"
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="Milliseconds" value="150"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="operation">Average operation time (ms).</label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <hr/>

            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="result-cache-time"
                           class="result"
                           type="text"
                           readonly=true
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="Milliseconds"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="result-cache-time">Expected Average Time using the Cache system (ms)</label>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="my-row">
                <div class="my-col-25">
                    <input id="result-cache-percent"
                           class="result"
                           type="text"
                           readonly=true
                           onchange="cacheCalculation()" onkeyup="cacheCalculation()"
                           placeholder="%"/>
                </div>

                <div class="my-col-75">
                    <label for="result-cache-percent">Expected improvement percentage (0-100)</label >
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<script>
    function cacheCalculation() {
        console.log("entra");
        var rs = parseFloat(document.getElementById('rs').value);
        var cacheRead = parseFloat(document.getElementById('cache-read').value);
        var cacheWrite = parseFloat(document.getElementById('cache-write').value);
        var operation = parseFloat(document.getElementById('operation').value);

        var result = (cacheRead + ((100 - rs)*(operation + cacheWrite)/100)).toFixed(2);

        document.getElementById('result-cache-time').value = result + "ms";
        document.getElementById('result-cache-percent').value = ((100 * operation / result) - 100).toFixed(2) + "%";
    }
    cacheCalculation();
</script>


<h2 id="long-answer">Long answer</h2>
<p>When anyone says about adding a cache to make any service faster I can only ask: &ldquo;how faster is it going to be?&rdquo;.
Usually I have no answer, just people angry with me.</p>]]></description></item></channel></rss>